The paper deals with the use of statistical information extracted from a large collection of text to answer subcognitive questions, which is a common approach in natural language processing and machine learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Among these, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the use of AI and NLP techniques to solve complex problems in language understanding and cognition.
